## 📖 Overview

This project implements an **Image Caption Generator** from scratch using deep learning. Given an input image, the model generates a natural language description of the visual content. The system supports platform-specific caption styles for Instagram, LinkedIn, Twitter, and Email.

The model is built using:
- **ResNet-50** as the CNN encoder for visual feature extraction
- **Bahdanau Attention Mechanism** to focus on relevant image regions
- **LSTM Decoder** for sequential caption generation
- **FastAPI** for serving the model as a REST API

---

## 🏗️ Architecture

```
Input Image [224x224]
      ↓
ResNet-50 Encoder (pretrained, frozen)
      ↓
Feature Map [49 regions × 2048 features]
      ↓
Bahdanau Attention Mechanism
      ↓
LSTM Decoder (word by word)
      ↓
Generated Caption
```

### Key Components

| Component | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| **Encoder** | ResNet-50 pretrained on ImageNet, outputs 49 spatial region features |
| **Attention** | Soft Bahdanau attention — learns which image regions to focus on per word |
| **Decoder** | LSTM with 512 hidden units, generates captions word by word |
| **Postprocessor** | Converts descriptions to platform-specific captions |

---

## ✨ Features

- **Image to Caption** — upload any image and get an instant description
- **Platform Specific** — generates captions styled for:
  - Instagram (casual, emoji, hashtags)
  - LinkedIn (professional, formal)
  - Twitter (short, punchy)
  - Email (descriptive, formal)
- **Attention Visualization** — see which image regions the model focused on
- **REST API** — FastAPI backend with Swagger UI
- **Resume Training** — checkpoint saving after every epoch

