## 🏋️ Training

### Local Training (CPU)
```bash
python train.py
```

### Google Colab Training (Recommended — free GPU)

Training on a laptop CPU takes ~4 hours per epoch. Use Google Colab's free T4 GPU for 10-15 minutes per epoch.

1. Open [Google Colab](https://colab.research.google.com)
2. Enable GPU: **Runtime → Change runtime type → T4 GPU**
3. Mount Google Drive:
```python
from google.colab import drive
drive.mount('/content/drive')
```
4. Upload your project zip and run training

### Training Configuration

Edit `config.py` to adjust hyperparameters:

```python
BATCH_SIZE    = 32       # images per batch
EPOCHS        = 20       # training epochs
LEARNING_RATE = 4e-4     # Adam learning rate
ENCODER_DIM   = 2048     # ResNet feature size
DECODER_DIM   = 512      # LSTM hidden size
ATTENTION_DIM = 512      # attention layer size
EMBED_DIM     = 512      # word embedding size
```

### Training Results

| Epoch | Train Loss | Val Loss |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| 1 | 3.62 | 3.00 |
| 5 | 2.37 | 2.38 |
| 10 | 2.00 | 2.22 |

