## 🔬 How It Works

### 1. Image Encoding
The ResNet-50 encoder processes the input image and extracts a feature map of shape `[49, 2048]` — representing 49 spatial regions each described by 2048 numbers.

### 2. Attention Mechanism
At each word generation step, the Bahdanau attention module computes a weighted sum over all 49 regions. Weights represent how much the model focuses on each region:
```
attention_weight = softmax(W * tanh(encoder_features + decoder_hidden))
context_vector   = sum(attention_weight * encoder_features)
```

### 3. Caption Generation
The LSTM decoder takes the context vector + previous word embedding and predicts the next word. This repeats until the `<end>` token is generated.

### 4. Platform Postprocessing
The raw description is converted to a platform-specific caption using the postprocessor module which applies tone, style, emojis, and hashtags.

